# pyenv
#   For a library or app, you might want to share your .python-version if you
#   use pyenv. Uncomment if you want to ignore it.
#.python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if you choose not to share it, uncomment the following line:
#Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   According to poetry documentation, it is recommended to include poetry.lock in version control.
#   poetry.lock

# pdm
#   According to pdm documentation, it is recommended to include pdm.lock in version control.
#   pdm.lock

# PEP 582; used by e.g. github.com/lincolnloop/layman and pdm
